-- Mantega to Eliminate IOF Tax on Auto Loans, IstoE Says
-- B y   M a t t h e w   B r i s t o w
-- 2012-05-21T20:40:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-21/mantega-to-eliminate-iof-tax-on-auto-loans-istoe-says-correct-.html
(Corrects name of the magazine’s website reporting the
information in headline in first paragraph.)  Brazilian Finance Minister  Guido Mantega  will eliminate the so-called IOF tax on auto loans as
part of a package of measures he will announce today to help the
car industry, Guilherme Barros, a columnist at Sao Paulo-based
IstoE Dinheiro  said  on the magazine’s website, without saying
how he obtained the information.  Mantega is scheduled to speak to reporters at 6pm Brasilia
time today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Matthew Bristow in Brasilia at 
 mbristow5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  